JOS – The Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Plateau State, Honourable Rufus Bature, has called on all key stakeholders, members and lovers of the party to rally round the state gubernatorial candidate, Dr Nantawe Yilwatda, to ensure victory for the APC in the 2023 elections. Bature made this call when the state Executive Committee paid a congratulatory visit to the party’s gubernatorial candidate, Dr Yilwatda, at his Rayfield residence. Bature pleaded with all those who contested with the candidate to see the reason to close ranks and collapse their lofty ideas and policies into those of the gubernatorial candidate for the overall interest of the party and Plateau State. -Advertisement- While emphasising the need for unity, Bature said the party remains one big family where there is room to accommodate everybody when he or she emerges victorious. Hon. Rufus Bature noted that in a big party as the APC, there are bound to be disagreements but the common denominator is the interest of Plateau state. He called on the gubernatorial candidate of the party to make every effort to reconcile with all the aggrieved aspirants in order to have a seamless campaign which would ensure victory for the party at all levels. He urged him to work the talk of his laudable policies especially as they relate to security, agriculture, education and all things that are noble.Responding, the gubernatorial candidate, Dr Nentawe Yilwatda, thanked the party Chairman and his entire exco for the honour of paying him the congratulatory and solidarity visit.He commended the party for midwifing successful primary elections which led to his emergence as the governorship candidate.He said as part of his reconciliation with all other contestants who lost at the primary election, he had visited all of them who are in town with the exception of two who are out of town and who he promised to visit after the National Convention of the party next week.He said he has a list of all other contestants from the House of Assembly to the Senate including those who won and lost and has placed personal calls to most of them.He said intends to further engage them at a dinner and bring them on board in the campaign council to be formed along with the party.He called on the party to organise a dinner session for all the gubernatorial aspirants where he would also be invited in order to further cement the relationship.He said he would fully engage the party on how to bring a new dimension into the campaign and a practical demonstration of what governance is all about.Dr Nentawe said he has a workable agenda and policies which are online and he is engaging all Plateau indigenes including those in the diaspora.He revealed that he has an invitation from Plateau indigenes in the United Kingdom for engagements and interface on his policies which he believes would also come from Plateau indigenes in other parts of the world.He said the party would do everything within the law to ensure its victory at the 2023 elections.The gubernatorial candidate concluded by saying that his focal point is to have a secured, united and prosperous Plateau state.